---
title: Chipotle Spiced Chicken with Mexican Potatoes and Roasted Veggies
description: You may have heard of a chipotle (pronounced “chi-pot-lay”), maybe you’ve even cooked with one before, but do you know exactly what a chipotle pepper is...? A chipotle pepper is simply a smoked, dried jalapeño. Their distinct smokey flavour works brilliantly as a marinade for the chicken, and we’ve put out the fire a little by serving it with a good dollop sour cream. Enjoy!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/chipotle-spiced-chicken-05e599ae-4b65ec6a.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/chipotle-spiced-chicken-5a858e9630006c2d20708d72-183aa6a1.pdf
time required: 40 minutes
servings: 2
cuisine: Mexican
